# FairBanks Community Reach — How the Model Works

Canonical operating model for FairBanks community work. Use this when writing copy, designing product flows, pitching FCHIP, or describing impact. Do not invent alternate programme names or reorder the cascade.

**Mission:** Connecting Care, Empowering Communities, Creating Lasting Impact.  
**Tagline:** Health for All — *Obulamu eri Bonna* · *Afya kwa Wote* · *Oburamu bwa Boona*  
**Slogan (docs/decks):** Your health, our mission.

## Principles

- **Health for All** — Care reaches every community member who needs it.
- **Communities First** — Communities identify needs, participate, and own solutions.
- **Empowerment for Sustainable Change** — Health gains link to livelihoods and lasting resilience.

## Core cascade (top → bottom)

1. **Community members** — Identify needs; participate in and own solutions.
2. **Community Health Workers (CHWs)** — Bridge communities to care: outreach, education, referrals, follow-up, data collection. (Include VHTs where Uganda context applies.)
3. **FairBanks Community Reach Programmes** — Outreach, health education, screening, maternal & child health, adolescent health, chronic care, home visits.
4. **FairBanks Medical Centre** — Clinical care, diagnostics, pharmacy, specialist support, referrals, quality assurance.
5. **Research · Partnerships · Skills development** — Evidence, innovation, academic/institutional partners, training, capacity building.
6. **Economic empowerment & sustainable communities** — Livelihoods, financial inclusion, IGAs, resilient families, healthy communities, sustainable development.

## Continuous loop

**Community needs & priorities** flow down the cascade; **services & solutions** flow back to communities.  
Loop actors: Communities · CHWs · FBCR Programmes · Medical Centre · Research · Empowerment — working together for lasting impact.

## Needs & priorities (inputs)

| Area | Includes |
|------|----------|
| **Preventive health** | Health promotion, immunisation, screening, early detection |
| **Education & awareness** | Health literacy, school health, community dialogues, behaviour change |
| **Vulnerable group support** | Women & mothers, children & adolescents, elderly, persons with disabilities, refugees, urban poor |

## Services & enablers (outputs)

| Area | Includes |
|------|----------|
| **Livelihoods & enterprise** | IGAs, savings groups, entrepreneurship, skills for jobs |
| **Data & feedback** | Community data, monitoring, learning, continuous improvement |
| **Partnerships & resources** | Government, NGOs & CBOs, academic institutions, donors & partners, private sector |

## How to use this rule

- Frame FairBanks as a **community health ecosystem**, not only a clinic.
- When describing FCHIP: it is the **intelligence layer** on this cascade—especially CHW data, programmes, medical centre records, and the data & feedback loop.
- Keep vulnerable groups, livelihoods, and multi-stakeholder partners visible in problem/impact copy where relevant.
- Prefer human language; preserve the cascade order if summarising the model.
